>> title: Mediterranean Pita Pizzas
>> servings: 4
>> prep time: 15 minutes
>> cook time: 15 minutes

1. Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).

2. Brush @wheat pita breads{6%whole} with @extra virgin olive oil{3%tbsp} on both sides.

3. In a small bowl, mix diced @tomatoes{2%large} with @garlic{2%cloves}, @oregano{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

4. Spread tomato mixture evenly over @wheat pita breads{6%whole}.

5. Top with @spinach leaves{2%cups} and @crumbled feta cheese{0.5%cup}.

6. Place on baking sheets and bake for 8-10 minutes until edges are crispy and @crumbled feta cheese{0.5%cup} is slightly golden.

7. Meanwhile, toss sweet potato wedges with @extra virgin olive oil{3%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

8. Roast @sweet potatoes{3%large} on a separate baking sheet for 25-30 minutes until tender.

9. Serve pizzas with roasted sweet potato wedges and cut vegetables with hummus.

10. Let kids help with toppings - they love making their own pizzas!

-- Category: Mediterranean
-- Cholesterol benefits: Whole wheat pita provides fiber, olive oil gives healthy fats, and the vegetables add antioxidants. Sweet potatoes are rich in fiber and potassium. This is a great interactive meal - kids love making their own pizzas and are more likely to try new toppings when they help prepare them.
